   and TI-81), and I'm learning Lisp (this week).
   I've actually participated in the International Olympiad in Informatics,
   a programming competition for high school students. I qualified to
   the Swedish final, where I ended up on the 13th place (of 30) with a 
   score of 15 points out of 24.
 * When I'm not programming, I'm reading. I recommend:
    * "Vurt" and "Pollen" by Jeff Noon
    * "The Shockwave Rider" by John Brunner (cyberpunk, written 1975!)
    * "Bone" by Jeff Smith
    * "The Tao of Pooh" by Benjamin Hoff
    * "Gödel, Escher, Bach" and "The Mind's I" by Douglas R. Hofstadter
    * Anything by Stephen Baxter, Douglas Adams and Terry Pratchett
    * "Rymdväktaren" ("The Space Guardian") and "Nyaga" by Peter Nilson.
      If you don't understand Swedish force a publishing company, with
      violence if necessary, to translate it =)
 * When I'm programming, I listen to music.
   The three best records ever:
    1) The Beatles: Sgt Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band
    2) Janis Joplin (with Full Tilt Boogie): Pearl
    3) The Beatles: The White Album.
   Sharing the fourth place:
    John Mayall: Jazz Blues Fusion
    Eric Clapton: 461 Ocean Boulevard
    Jimi Hendrix, B.B. King, and quite a few more.
   Generally, I favour blues and rock, preferably from the seventies, and 
   also psychadelic pop.
 * I'm a member of the DNRC, where I am Commander of the Nyaga Project.
